claim.claim-text:
A method for rigging a control surface (12) of an aircraft (2), wherein the control surface (12) is movable relative to a reference structure (4) of the aircraft (2) by means of at least one actuator (18), the method comprising the steps of:
- fixing a first rigging component (20) relative to the reference structure (4)
- fixing a second rigging component (22) relative to the control surface (12);
- connecting a mobile control unit (38) to the at least one actuator (18);
- providing a command signal by using input means (44) of the control unit (38);
- generating an actuator signal by means of the control unit (3 8) for inducing a motion of the control surface (12) depending on the provided command signal;
- indicating a relative spatial position of the first and second rigging components (20, 22) by means of a light beam between the first and second rigging components (20, 22); and
- adjusting the relative position between the control surface (12) and the reference structure (4) based on the indicated relative spatial position.
